headline: 2 Reasons to Like INTU and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: Intuit’s 28.8% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 23%, and its stock price has climbed to $781.60 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
